						<div class="postbody"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RANDU" class="postlink">RANDU: A Cautionary Tale</a><br /><br />Also, it may be worth running your PRNG for a while before you start testing for cycles. It is possible to enter a cycle from a seed value outside that cycle. (Also, obviously if you want to test longer cycles you can reimplement it on a modern computer. I usually do this first, and then implement it on the target hardware after.)</div>

